						               													<description>Lachaino is a deduction game for two players. Each player makes a chain of consecutive numbers that fills a square grid; for example, if 10x10 grids are used, each player fills a grid with the numbers 1-100 with each number adjacent to the previous one.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a turn a player specifies a 2x2 section of the grid and the opposing player gives the product of the four numbers it contains, broken down into prime factors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object is to reconstruct the opponent's chain in the fewest number of guesses. If a player finds that one or both ends of the chain are ambiguous due to all four end numbers being in a 2x2 section, they may leave these undefined for a half-guess penalty each.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was first presented in Hopscotch #65 and then printed in World Game Review #8.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
